Civil Status

Civil status registration

Δ

Algerian parent (s) must report the birth of a newborn to the Consulate General of Algeria in the country of birth;

12-s is an extract of a birth certificate, it is compulsory for the issuance of a biometric passport or ID card;

The marriage in the United States of an Algerian National must be registered at the Consulate General of Algeria in New York. A family book (livret de famille) is issued after registration & is free of charge;

All related documents can be filed in person without a prior appointment or by mail;

Applications sent by mail should be accompanied by a Priority Mail return envelope from USPS for a faster and safer return of your documents;

Incomplete applications sent by mail will not be accepted and will be returned to the sender.

