FOR AN APPLICANT BORN IN ALGERIA

You can get it:

Online through the Ministry of the Interior website (read more about how to apply online for 12s);

Or from the Town Hall of your place of birth (applying in person or by power of attorney issued by the consulate).

For further information about this service, please do not hesitate to contact us

FOR AN APPLICANT BORN IN USA

Required documents

Application form duly completed and signed;

Original full birth certificate or certified copy from the city hall (must include time of birth);

A copy of the applicant's proof of Algerian nationality and identity (Passport or National ID or Consular card or Military card)(if minor, parent's Algerian ID);

Family Book (if available).

Make sure, the first and last name of the parents shown on the child’s birth certificate is the same as it appears on the Algerian Civil Status register.

For further information about this service, please do not hesitate to contact us

FOR AN APPLICANT BORN IN ANOTHER COUNTRY

Required documents

Application form duly completed and signed;

Original or certified copy of the applicant's full birth certificate issued by the country of Birth;

A copy of the applicant's proof of Algerian nationality and identity (Passport or National ID or Consular card or Military card)(if minor, parent's Algerian ID);

Copy of the Family Book (if available).

Make sure, the first and last name of the parents shown on the child’s birth certificate is the same as it appears on the Algerian Civil Status register.

For further information about this service, please do not hesitate to contact us

In the event of the death of an Algerian in the United States of America, the Consulate General guides and assists the family of the deceased in the administrative formalities for the transfer of the mortal remains to Algeria which is (Paperwork) dealt with by the Funeral Services appointed by the deceased's family or relatives.

The Consulate General proceeds with the transcription and the issuance of an Algerian death certificate as well as the Authorisation for the transfer of the remains "Autorisation de Transfert de corps".

Required documents

Death report duly completed and signed;

Birth certificate of the deceased;

Medical letter issued by the department of health (non-infection or non-communicable disease);

Original death certificate issued by the US authorities;

Embalming certificate issued by the funeral services;

Transit permit issued by the City Hall;

A certificate stating that the body has been laid out according to Muslim rituals;

A copy of the deceased proof of Algerian nationality and identity (Passport or National ID or Consular card or Military card);

Airway bill (flight itinerary);

Family Book (if available).

Make sure, the first and last names of the deceased and his parents shown on the death certificate are the same as they appear on the Algerian Civil Status register.

For further information about this service, please do not hesitate to contact us

