DIVORCE REGISTRATION

Regardless of the place of marriage, a divorce pronounced in the United States of America or by any other foreign judicial authority, cannot produce its effects in Algeria if it is not recognized by an Algerian court.

The procedure of recognition is called "Exequatur" and it is conducted in Algeria by the applicant who may be represented by a lawyer.

For further information about this service, please do not hesitate to contact us

MARRIAGE REGISTRATION

Required documents

Descriptive form duly completed and signed;

Original American marriage certificate;

A copy of the applicant's proof of Algerian nationality and identity (Passport or National ID or Consular card or Military card);

Original birth certificates of both spouses (less than three months old).

For further information about this service, please do not hesitate to contact us

